Network Discovery protocols

Simple Service Discovery Protocol (SSDP) is used for service discovery in UPnP environments

All join notifications service (AJNS) enables communication between IoT devices

mDNS resolves host names to IP addresses on a LAN


In the Display Filter, enter: ((!(ssdp)) && !(ajns)) && !(mdns)
Go to the right hand side of the display filter and select the + sign

Enter the Label: NoNetDisc
Enter the comment: "No SSDP, AJNS, or mDNS" to describe the filter button, then click OK

Over on the right hand side, you will see your button
